<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1930,2029]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1967,1993]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from the Latin, 
<emphasis box="[861,922,1968,1993]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">arcus</emphasis>
(= bow, shaped like a bow), referring to the concavity on ventral margin of valva in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
